 Swing/AWT X11 toolkit initialization inside the native image, not from missing `com.mchange` library metadata.\\n\\n## Root cause by failing test\\n\\n### `propertyBoundTextFieldSyncsFromTheBean()`\\nThis failed with `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: sun/awt/X11/XErrorHandlerUtil` while `java.desktop` was initializing `sun.awt.X11GraphicsEnvironment` and `sun.awt.X11.XToolkit`.\\n\\nRoot cause: the generated test constructs `PropertyBoundTextField` and uses `SwingUtilities`, which forces native-image execution down the Linux X11 AWT/Swing path. That path depends on JDK-internal `sun.awt.X11.*` classes and platform GUI initialization. This is a native-image/X11 platform issue, not missing reachability metadata for `com.mchange:mchange-commons-java`.\\n\\n### `propertyBoundTextFieldWritesUserChangesBackToTheBean()`\\nThis failed with `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class sun.awt.X11.XToolkit` when checking or entering the EDT.\\n\\nRoot cause: same as above. The first X11 toolkit initialization failure poisoned subsequent Swing access, so the second test failed immediately when `SwingUtilities` touched the toolkit.\\n\\n## Codex log assessment\\n\\nThe Codex metadata-fix log shows it kept chasing JDK Swing/AWT internals for this GUI path, adding metadata for classes such as `java.awt.GraphicsEnvironment` and `sun.awt.SunToolkit`, but the final Gradle failure still ended in X11 toolkit initialization errors (`sun.awt.X11.XErrorHandlerUtil` / `sun.awt.X11.XToolkit`).\\n\\nThat indicates the remaining problem is not unresolved library metadata for `com.mchange`; it is an unsupported or unsuitable native Swing/X11 execution path for this generated test.\\n\\n## Intervention applied\\n\\nRemoved the generated test file:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.2.15/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated suite still exercises real, non-GUI library behaviors and passed after removing only this Swing/X11-specific test. Preserving the remaining generated tests and support keeps coverage for the metadata-relevant code paths that do work in native image, while dropping only the platform-dependent GUI scenario that is not a reliable metadata signal for this library.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter removing `PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`, the coordinate passed with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.2.15 --stacktrace`\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2065:      \"iterations\": 30,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2067:      \"generated_loc\": 2008,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2070:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 14.85\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2085:    \"status\": \"success_with_intervention\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2088:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2091:            \"coverageRatio\": 0.952381,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:2096:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_suppo