ics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6667:    \"status\": \"success_with_intervention\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6670:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6673:            \"coverageRatio\": 0.928571,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6678:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6683:        \"coverageRatio\": 0.935484,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6711:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.apache.ivy:ivy:2.5.2\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe native test run failed in three places after Codex's metadata-fix attempt:\\n\\n- `IvyAuthenticatorTest` failed for a non-metadata reason and was removed.\\n- `IvySettingsTest.initializesBundledResourcesAndDefaultMatchers()` is still failing for missing native-image support around Ivy's bundled settings resources and dynamically loaded default implementation classes.\\n- `MainTest.launchesConfiguredMainClassWithResolvedArguments()` is still failing because Ivy's default settings load bundled XML resources that are not all present in the native image.\\n\\n## Root cause by failing test\\n\\n### 1. `IvyAuthenticatorTest.installsWithModernAndLegacyAuthenticatorDiscovery()`\\n\\n**Classification:** not metadata-related\\n\\n**Root cause:** this test depends on Ivy reaching into private JDK `java.net.Authenticator` internals (`theAuthenticator` on the legacy path and reflective `getDefault()` access on the modern path). That is a JDK/native-image encapsulation issue around private platform internals, not missing Ivy library metadata.\\n\\nThe Gradle failure here was the null authentication result, not a missing metadata registration error from Ivy itself. The Codex log also shows it tried to paper over this with test-only reflection support for `java.net.Authenticator`, which confirms the failure was about test access to JDK internals rather than missing reachability metadata for the library.\\n\\n**Intervention:** removed `tests/src/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.2/src/test/java/org_apache_ivy/ivy/IvyAuthenticatorTest.java` and removed the related `java.net.Authenticator` entry from `tests/src/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/ivy-tests-only/reflect-config.json`.\\n\\n### 2. `IvySettingsTest.initializesBundledResourcesAndDefaultMatchers()`\\n\\n**Classification:** metadata-related\\n\\n**Root cause:** Ivy initializes its default settings by loading bundled XML/properties resources and then resolving many implementation classes by string name through `IvySettings.typeDef(...)`. In the failing native image, those resources/classes were not fully available.\\n\\nThe failure output shows both symptoms:\\n\\n- bundled settings resources are expected from `resource:/org/apache/ivy/core/settings/...`\\n- many default implementation classes cannot be loaded, for example:\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.matcher.GlobPatternMatcher`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.latest.LatestLexicographicStrategy`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.latest.LatestRevisionStrategy`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.latest.LatestTimeStrategy`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.version.ExactVersionMatcher`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.version.PatternVersionMatcher`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.version.SubVersionMatcher`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.version.ChainVersionMatcher`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.resolver.FileSystemResolver`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.resolver.URLResolver`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.plugins.resolver.IBiblioResolver`\\n  - `org.apache.ivy.core.cache.DefaultRepositoryCacheManager`\\n  - and other default resolver/conflict/OSGi classes listed in the Gradle output\\n\\nBecause the default matcher registration depends on those string-driven lookups, `settings.getMatcher(PatternMatcher.GLOB)` ends up `null`.\\n\\n**Why Codex could not resolve it cleanly:** the metadata-fix workflow is tuned for explicit `Missing*RegistrationError` reports. Here Ivy is loading classes and resources indirectly from bundled config files, so native-image reported generic \\\"class not found\\\" and missing-resource failures instead of precise registration suggestions. That left Codex without a narrow, trustworthy metadata delta to apply automatically.\\n\\n### 3. `MainTest.launchesConfiguredMainClassWithResolvedArguments()`\\n\\n**Classification:** metadata-related for the reported failure\\n\\n**Root cause:** Ivy's default startup path loads `resource:/org/apache/ivy/core/settings/ivysettings.xml`, which in turn includes other bundled settings files. The reported failure is the missing bundled resource:\\n\\n- `org/apache/ivy/core/settings/ivysettings-public.xml`\\n\\nThe same settings-loading path is tied to the broader missing bundled-settings support seen in `IvySettingsTest`. The Codex log also shows it diagnosed a resource gap first and then ran into additional string-based Ivy type loading from the same default settings flow.\\n\\n**Why Codex could not resolve it cleanly:** this was not a single missing resource. Ivy's default config is layered, and the native run surfaced one missing include (`ivysettings-public.xml`) while the surrounding log shows additional missing default-setting classes. Codex could not finish because the failures came from chained resource includes plus string-based class loading rather than direct metadata error hints.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is still useful and should stay in place:\\n\\n- `IvySettingsTest` and `MainTest` are exercising real Ivy behavior, not scaffold-only code.\\n- They expose genuine reachability gaps in Ivy's bundled default-settings initialization path.\\n- The other generated tests (`ConfiguratorTest`, `MemoryUtilTest`, `IvyTest`, and the remaining `MainTest`/`IvySettingsTest` coverage) still provide valid signal for future manual metadata completion.\\n- Removing the metadata-related tests would hide real native-image compatibility problems instead of documenting them.\\n\\n## Files changed during this intervention\\n\\n- Removed `tests/src/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.2/src/test/java/org_apache_ivy/ivy/IvyAuthenticatorTest.java`\\n- Updated `tests/src/org.apache.ivy/ivy/2.5.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/ivy-tests-only/reflect-config.json` to drop the now-unused `java.net.Authenticator` test-only reflection entry\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6717:      \"iterations\": 6,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6719:      \"generated_loc\": 353,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6722:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 13.6\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6737:    \"status\": \"success\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6740:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:6743:         