metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9228:            \"coverageRatio\": 0.666667,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9233:        \"coverageRatio\": 0.914286,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9261:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe native image built successfully, and the remaining failures were two native-runtime behavioral assertions rather than missing reachability metadata. There was no `Missing*RegistrationError` in the Gradle failure output. The generated support should therefore be kept, but the two unsupported native-only tests were removed.\\n\\nI also confirmed that the generated test suite passes on the JVM and that `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA --stacktrace` passes after removing the two failing native-only tests.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. `org.jboss.logmanager.LogManagerTest > readConfigurationFallsBackToLogManagerClassLoaderWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsConfigurator()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** `LogManager.construct(...)` uses `Class.forName(name, true, contextClassLoader)` first and then falls back to the `LogManager` class loader. In the native image, the assertion `rejectingClassLoader.rejectedClassLoadAttempted` stayed `false`, even though the configurator was still instantiated successfully.\\n- **Interpretation:** this test depends on observing a custom `ClassLoader.loadClass(...)` rejection path for an image-contained class. That is a native-image class-loading behavior difference, not missing metadata. If metadata were missing, the failure would have been a registration error or reflective instantiation failure, not a plain `assertThat(...).isTrue()` failure.\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and its test-only helpers from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/LogManagerTest.java`.\\n\\n### 2. `org.jboss.logmanager.formatters.Formatters12Test > extendedExceptionFormattingUsesClassLoadingFallbacksAndClassResourceLookup()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** the native failure was again a boolean assertion (`loadedFromBytes`, `rejectedSystemTargetAttempted`, or `classResourceRequested`) staying `false`, not a missing registration error. This test tries to verify that `%E` formatting forces a custom context class loader to byte-define a target class and then performs `.class` resource lookup through that loader.\\n- **Interpretation:** the formatter output path is preserved, but the test relies on runtime-observable custom class loading and resource lookup behavior that native image does not preserve in the same way for image-contained classes. The native image already built successfully, so this is not evidence of missing metadata.\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and the test-only helper loader/classes that existed solely for it from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/formatters/Formatters12Test.java`.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still exercises meaningful `jboss-logmanager` behavior that is relevant to reachability metadata:\\n\\n- context-class-loader-based configurator and locator instantiation still has coverage\\n- bootstrap fallback for exception formatting still has coverage\\n- privileged exception class resource lookup still has coverage\\n- property-based handler/filter/formatter/error-manager configuration still has coverage\\n- serialization-related coverage for the map implementations still has coverage\\n- default configuration lookup and typed array handling still have coverage\\n\\nIn short, only the two tests that depended on native-image-incompatible custom class-loading observability were removed. The rest of the generated suite still validates real library behavior and should be preserved.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9267:      \"iterations\": 10,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9269:      \"generated_loc\": 718,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9272:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 26.16\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9287:    \"status\": \"success_with_intervention\",\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9290:      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9293:            \"coverageRatio\": 0.9375,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9298:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9303:        \"coverageRatio\": 0.942857,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9331:      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe post-generation failures had two different causes:\\n\\n1. `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()` in the Codex metadata-fix log was **metadata-related**.\\n2. `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` in the final Gradle failure was **not metadata-related**; it depended on JVM class-loader fallback behavior that does not hold under Native Image.\\n\\nI removed the generated `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` test and kept the rest of the generated support.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. Codex log failure: metadata-related\\n\\nThe Codex log shows a `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` from:\\n\\n- `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()`\\n\\nMissing entry reported by Native Image:\\n\\n- `java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock$Sync.readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream)`\\n\\nThat failure came from Java deserialization of `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap`, so it was a real reachability-metadata gap rather than a bad test. This support should be preserved because it covers an actual native-image requirement for the library's serialization path.\\n\\n### 2. Remaining Gradle failure: not metadata-related\\n\\nThe remaining failing test was:\\n\\n- `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()`\\n\\nThis failed on:\\n\\n- `assertThat(rejectingClassLoader.wasRejected()).isTrue()`\\n\\nRoot cause:\\n\\n- The test assumes the formatter will first try to resolve the stack-frame class through the thread context class loader, observe a `ClassNotFoundException`, and only then fall back to the caller loader.\\n- In Native Image, class resolution for already-linked image classes does not preserve that JVM class-loading interaction in the same way. The formatted stack trace is still produced, but the custom rejecting loader is never asked to load the class, so `wasRejected()` stays `false`.\\n- No `Missing*RegistrationError` was reported for this failure, so this was not a metadata problem.\\n\\nThis is therefore a Native Image class-loading/runtime-semantics issue in the generated test, and removing that generated test was the correct intervention.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated support still exercises real library behavior and should remain in place:\\n\\n- serialization coverage for `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap` and `FastCopyHashMap`\\n- resource lookup coverage for `DefaultConfigurationLocator`\\n- formatter/resource coverage in `Formatters12Test`\\n- configuration loading and component instantiation coverage in `LogManagerTest` and `PropertyConfiguratorTest`\\n\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata-related formatter fallback test, the coordinate passed again with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\n- `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\n\\nSo the generated metadata-backed support is still valuable and should be kept; only the unsupported caller-loader fallback assertion needed to be dropped.\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9337:      \"iterations\": 16,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9339:      \"generated_loc\": 704,\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json:9342:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 26.04\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_