tadata-related failures for `org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.22`. The remaining native test failures were all non-metadata issues, so I removed only the generated tests that exercised those unsupported behaviors.\\n\\nRemoved generated tests:\\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.22/src/test/java/lombok/launch/AgentTest.java`\\n- `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoaderTest#loadsResourcesFromShadowAwareParentClasspath`\\n- `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoaderTest#skipsShadowEntriesWhenOverridesAreConfigured`\\n- `lombok.launch.ShadowClassLoaderTest#reusesAlreadyLoadedClassesAndHandlesConcurrentDuplicateDefinitions`\\n\\n## Root cause of each removed failure\\n\\n### `AgentTest#premainInvokesShadowLoadedAgentLauncher`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe test fails with:\\n- `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Unknown protocol: resource:/lombok/launch/Agent.class`\\n\\nLombok's agent path goes through `lombok.patcher.ClassRootFinder`, which expects a class location URL that behaves like a normal jar/file URL. Inside the native test image it receives a `resource:/...` URL instead, so the Eclipse patcher path aborts before any metadata lookup is relevant.\\n\\n### `AgentTest#agentmainInvokesShadowLoadedAgentLauncherAndRequestsReload`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThis fails for the same reason as `premain`: the agent bootstrap logic depends on URL/protocol handling that is different inside Native Image, and it dies on `resource:/...` before metadata could help.\\n\\n### `ShadowClassLoaderTest#loadsResourcesFromShadowAwareParentClasspath`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe test expects JVM-style discovery of temp-dir parent resources and shadow entries via `ShadowClassLoader#getResources(...)`. In the native executable, those runtime-created parent resources are not enumerated the same way, so the expected resource list is empty. This is a resource-loading/runtime-behavior mismatch, not missing reachability metadata.\\n\\n### `ShadowClassLoaderTest#skipsShadowEntriesWhenOverridesAreConfigured`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThis is the same family of issue as the previous test: it depends on JVM resource lookup behavior across runtime-created parent class loaders and override directories. In Native Image the expected shadow resource is not found, so the assertion fails. No missing reflection/resource registration error is involved.\\n\\n### `ShadowClassLoaderTest#reusesAlreadyLoadedClassesAndHandlesConcurrentDuplicateDefinitions`\\nNon-metadata failure.\\n\\nThe test intentionally defines the same predefined class through multiple `ShadowClassLoader` instances. Native Image reports:\\n- `UnsupportedFeatureError: A predefined class can be loaded (defined) at runtime only once by a single class loader.`\\n\\nThat is an explicit Native Image limitation around predefined/runtime-defined classes, not a metadata gap.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is still useful and should stay in place because the surviving tests continue to validate real Lombok native behavior:\\n- `AnnotationProcessorHiderAnnotationProcessorTest` proves the shadow-loaded annotation processor path works with the generated metadata.\\n- `MainTest` proves `lombok.launch.Main` can still delegate to the shadow-loaded core main class inside Native Image.\\n- `PatchFixesHiderUtilTest` still exercises Lombok's reflective utility path.\\n- `ShadowClassLoaderTest#loadsClassesFromPrependedParents` still covers supported shadow class loading behavior.\\n\\nThe generated test resources under `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.22/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/` are therefore still needed by the tests that remain.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata tests, the coordinate passes:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.22`\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2123-3b33bb3d/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.j